{
  "texts": [
    "This step sometimes involves giving a name, for instance the coining of the term 'sexual harassment'.",
    "Semantically produced epistemic injustice, as outlined above, relates to a dysfunction in this process which in turn leads to hermeneutical disadvantages and harms.",
    "It points to instances where the conceptual vocabulary either is unavailable or is available but excludes things that really ought to fall under its umbrella (Medina, 2017, p.45).",
    "The second step in the diagram describes the recognition of the concept as part of the collective hermeneutical resources.",
    "It illustrates that certain conceptual resources might very well be part of the hermeneutical resources available to members of a particular group, but not to the collective (Dotson, 2014; Medina, 2017; Pohlhaus, 2012)."
  ]
}